Ponderosa first appeared as a [[census designated place]] in the [[2010 U.S. census]].<ref name=2010CensusCA/>

The [[2020 United States census]] reported that Ponderosa had a population of 51. The population density was {{convert|62.9|PD/sqmi|PD/km2|sp=us|adj=off}}. The racial makeup of Ponderosa was 42 (82%) [[White Americans|White]], 0 (0%) [[African Americans|African American]], 4 (7.8%) [[Native Americans in the United States|Native American]], 0 (0%) [[Asian Americans|Asian]], 0 (0%) [[Pacific Islander Americans|Pacific Islander]], 1 (2%) from [[Race (United States Census)|other races]], and 4 (8%) from two or more races. [[Hispanic and Latino Americans|Hispanic or Latino]] of any race were 6 persons (12%).<ref name=DP1>{{cite web |title=Ponderosa CDP, California; DP1: Profile of General Population and Housing Characteristics - 2020 Census of Population and Housing |url=https://data.census.gov/table/DECENNIALDP2020.DP1?g=1600000US0658134 |website=US Census Bureau |access-date=May 31, 2025}}</ref>

There were 25 households, and the average household size was 2.04.<ref name=DP1/>

The age distribution was 7 people (13.7%) under the age of 18, 0 people (0%) aged 18 to 24, 6 people (12%) aged 25 to 44, 17 people (33%) aged 45 to 64, and 21 people (41%) who were 65{{nbsp}}years of age or older. The median age was 62.5{{nbsp}}years. There were 34 males and 17 females.<ref name=DP1/>

There were 142 housing units at an average density of {{convert|175.1|/mi2|/km2|disp=preunit|units&nbsp;|units|}}, of which 25 (18%) were occupied year round and 104 (73%) were used seasonally. Of the occupied housing units, 24 (96%) were owner-occupied, and 1 (4%) were occupied by renters.<ref name=DP1/>

